&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 3&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;carnival&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means a public event or celebration, usually involving processions, music, dancing, and the use of costumes. (मेला, उत्सव)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The city holds a grand carnival every year to celebrate the harvest season.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Fest&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to a festival or a gathering to celebrate something, often with food, music, and entertainment. (उत्सव)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;We attended the Oktoberfest in Munich, which is a famous beer fest.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, we can infer that the word &amp;quot;carnival&amp;quot; is synonymous with &amp;quot;fest&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Heavily&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;भारी&lt;/span&gt;): To a great degree or with great weight.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; It was raining heavily, making it difficult to walk outside.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Funeral&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;अंतिम संस्कार&lt;/span&gt;): A ceremony or service held shortly after a person&amp;#39;s death.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;Many people attended the funeral to pay their respects.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sedate&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;शांत&lt;/span&gt;): Calm, dignified, and unhurried.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The sedate town was a perfect place for relaxation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; sanctimonious&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meaning of the idiom &lt;strong&gt;holier than thou&lt;/strong&gt; is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;characterized by an attitude of moral superiority&lt;/strong&gt;.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ex. They had quite a critical, holier-than-thou approach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sanctimonious&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;making a show of&lt;strong&gt; being morally superior &lt;/strong&gt;to other people.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Synonyms - Self-righteous, &lt;strong&gt;holier-than-thou,&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;pious, pietistic.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Other options may look similar to the meaning of morality but option 4 is the most suitable answer to the given expression.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;sanctimonious.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/confusion-points-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Confusion Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We may get confused about the option religious, however the meaning concentrates more upon the&lt;strong&gt; superior&amp;nbsp;morality &lt;/strong&gt;of a person.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;venom&amp;quot;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Poison: &lt;/strong&gt;A substance that is capable of causing the illness or death of a living organism when introduced or absorbed. (विष)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;Consuming rat poison can be fatal to humans.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Venom: &lt;/strong&gt;A toxic substance secreted by animals such as snakes, spiders, and scorpions, typically injected into prey or aggressors by biting or stinging. (जहर)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The venom of a King Cobra can be deadly to humans if not treated immediately.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Option 2&amp;quot;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Elixir: A magical or medicinal potion supposed to have the power to cure all illnesses. (अमृत)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: In ancient myths, heroes often seek an elixir for immortality.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Bitter: Having a sharp, pungent taste or smell; not sweet. (कड़वा)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: The bitter taste of raw neem leaves is said to have medicinal properties.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Fatal: Causing death. (घातक)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: The accident on the highway was fatal for two passengers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 4)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;i.e.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;moderate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-62d2fe9b-7fff-027c-d67b-8576d87c1382&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border: none; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; width: 40px; height: 35px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;35&quot; src=&quot;https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/28i2H4qZUMqoricKhH6aaLqxFoqVxqpmaJpMBy62DoGJbWBmmYJxPuBF6Wq_gGqfYCkpEpr0WIm9NnvtUCdNGqm-1_wqVyF46346wBwUiFK7AiZX8LxkL7abs3B0GOqVQ9Wwde-d&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px;&quot; width=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Explanation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;abrupt&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;means sudden and unexpected.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Let&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;us&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;explore&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;options&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;:
	&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Quick&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;acting or capable of acting with speed.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Hasty&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;acting too quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Sudden&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;made or brought about in a short time.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Moderate&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;average in amount, intensity, quality, or degree.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hence&lt;/span&gt;, the option &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;moderate&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is an incorrect replacement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-2eea6fcf-7fff-965f-4d8b-ce2ec37ed1a8&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border: none; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; width: 120px; height: 40px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;40&quot; src=&quot;https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/sWn1oC6mlNsROP-zVXMvAlT_Fqes0HlQMQeDtmr94LuJqLv7dOdQtJ2Q7iQ1JS5REaHqKFCFChrBmdKT4svOFMwg4y1JdWWC5pg4X0ls_aEdE-_EV4rBZGTOua1aQGpEgOl5QU9H&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px;&quot; width=&quot;120&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;synonyms&lt;/span&gt; of the word &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Abrupt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39; are &amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;sudden, unanticipated, unexpected, unforeseen, unlooked-for&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antonyms&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Abrupt&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; are &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;moderate,​&amp;nbsp;gentle, gradual, soft&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Its&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first known use&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;was&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;in&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the year&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;1565&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Examples&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Abrupt&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; in a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;sentence&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;:
	&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The time at which the surface discharge bridges over the silicon plate corresponds to an &lt;strong&gt;abrupt&lt;/strong&gt; decrease in voltage across the plate&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The experimentally known phenomenon of an &lt;strong&gt;abrupt&lt;/strong&gt; transition from slow conducive to fast convective&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Compromise, cooperation between people.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The idiom &amp;quot;give and take&amp;quot; refers to a situation where both parties involved are willing to compromise and cooperate with each other.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ऐसी स्थिति जहां शामिल दोनों पक्ष एक-दूसरे के साथ समझौता करने और सहयोग करने को तैयार हों।
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;There has to be a tremendous amount of give and take in negotiations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It implies a mutual exchange of concessions or benefits.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrase is often used in the context of negotiations or relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Grammatically, &amp;quot;give and take&amp;quot; is a noun phrase, and it can be used as a standalone idiom or as part of a sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, it is clear that the option 2 explains the given idiom correctly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence,&lt;strong&gt; the correct answer is option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;Compromise&amp;quot; means&amp;nbsp;an agreement that is reached when each person gets part, but not all, of what he/she wanted. (&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;समझौता)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;Cooperation&amp;quot; means&amp;nbsp;an act or instance of working or acting together for a common purpose or benefit. (&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;सहयोग)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Tell something that should be kept secret.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;spill the beans&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;means to reveal a secret or confidential information. (किसी गुप्त या गोपनीय जानकारी को प्रकट करना)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;Don&amp;#39;t &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;spill the beans&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; in front of your parents.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This idiom is often used in informal situations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrase&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;spill the beans&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is often used in a negative context, as it implies that someone has revealed something that they shouldn&amp;#39;t have.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is Option 2.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Philosopher&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct option that can be used as a one-word substitute for the given group of words is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Philosopher&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Philosopher: &lt;/strong&gt;a person who studies and loves wisdom and seeks to understand the fundamental nature of knowledge, reality, and existence.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: Socrates, Plato, and Aristotle are some of the most famous &lt;strong&gt;philosophers &lt;/strong&gt;in history.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Philanderer: &lt;/strong&gt;a person who engages in many love affairs, especially frivolous or casual ones.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: He was known as a &lt;strong&gt;philanderer&lt;/strong&gt;, always chasing after different women.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Astrologer:&lt;/strong&gt; a person who studies the positions and aspects of celestial bodies to make predictions about human affairs and natural phenomena.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: She consulted with an &lt;strong&gt;astrologer &lt;/strong&gt;to determine the best time to make a major life change.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Psychologist:&lt;/strong&gt; a person who studies human behavior and mental processes, including perception, cognition, emotion, and motivation.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: The &lt;strong&gt;psychologist &lt;/strong&gt;helped the patient work through their feelings of anxiety and depression.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Mariticide&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s explore the meaning of the marked option:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mariticide:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36); &quot;&gt;the killing of one&amp;#39;s husband. or {&lt;/span&gt;Mariticide (from Latin&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;maritus&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;quot;husband&amp;quot; + &lt;strong&gt;-cide, from caedere &amp;quot;to cut, to kill&amp;quot;)&lt;/strong&gt;}&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, from the&lt;strong&gt; above-given explanation&lt;/strong&gt;, it can be concluded that the correct answer is &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s explore the meaning of the other&amp;nbsp;options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regicide -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;a person who kills a king (वह व्यक्ति जो किसी राजा की हत्या करता हो)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Uxoricide-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;a man who kills his wife.&amp;nbsp;(किसी की पत्नी की हत्या)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Matricide -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;a crime in which a person kills their mother (एक अपराध जिसमें एक व्यक्ति अपनी माँ को मारता है)&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 1&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Imitation&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means something that is a copy or reproduction of an original item. (नकली)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The painting in the gallery was an imitation of a famous masterpiece.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Fake&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to something that is not genuine and is made to look like something else. (नकली)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;He bought a fake watch thinking it was a real Rolex.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Real&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;वास्तविक&lt;/span&gt;): Actually existing as a thing or occurring in fact.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The real diamond sparkled brilliantly under the light.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Genuine&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;असली&lt;/span&gt;): Truly what something is said to be; authentic.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;She showed me a genuine piece of ancient pottery.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Original&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;मूल&lt;/span&gt;): Present or existing from the beginning; first or earliest.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The original manuscript of the novel was found in the author&amp;#39;s attic.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;outstanding&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s take a look at the given words:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mediocre&lt;/strong&gt;: average or ordinary; not very good

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence&lt;/strong&gt;: The &lt;strong&gt;mediocre &lt;/strong&gt;athlete didn&amp;#39;t win any medals at the competition.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Excellent &lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;extremely good; outstanding
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Sentence :&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;She was an&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;excellent &lt;/strong&gt;singer.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Poor&lt;/strong&gt;: not good in quality or performance
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence&lt;/strong&gt;: The &lt;strong&gt;poor &lt;/strong&gt;team didn&amp;#39;t score any points in the game.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outstanding&lt;/strong&gt;: very good; exceptional
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence&lt;/strong&gt;: The &lt;strong&gt;outstanding &lt;/strong&gt;athlete received a trophy for their impressive performance.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Average&lt;/strong&gt;: typical or ordinary; not exceptional
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence&lt;/strong&gt;: The &lt;strong&gt;average &lt;/strong&gt;athlete placed in the middle of the rankings.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the given meanings and examples, we can conclude that &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;mediocre,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;poor,&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;average&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; are not synonyms for &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;excellent&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, &lt;strong&gt;option 3: outstanding&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct synonym.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct sentence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; : &amp;quot;&lt;em&gt;The athlete was excellent in the semifinals and even managed to put on an &lt;strong&gt;outstanding &lt;/strong&gt;performance at the championship game&lt;/em&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mediocre&lt;/strong&gt;: औसत या साधारण; बहुत अच्छी नहीं&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Excellent &lt;/strong&gt;: अत्यंत अच्छी; उत्कृष्ट&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Poor&lt;/strong&gt;: गुणवत्ता या प्रदर्शन में अच्छी नहीं&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outstanding&lt;/strong&gt;: बहुत अच्छा; असाधारण&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Average&lt;/strong&gt;: सामान्य; असाधारण नहीं&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए अर्थ और उदाहरणों से हम निश्चित हो सकते हैं कि &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;mediocre&lt;/span&gt;,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;poor&lt;/span&gt;,&amp;quot; और &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;average&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot; &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;excellent&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot; के समानार्थी शब्द नहीं हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, &lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;outstanding&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;सही समानार्थी शब्द है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Gregarious&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s refer to all the given options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Gregarious&lt;/span&gt;: (of a person) fond of company; sociable.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Potable :&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;A liquid that is suitable for drinking&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chronology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;The arrangement of events or dates in the order of their occurrence&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nostalgia&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;A sentimental longing or wistful affection for a period in the past&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the above words&amp;#39; meanings, it can be concluded that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Gregarious&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;A person fond of company&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hence, the correct choice is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;without a reasonable explanation.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;If we read the sentence, &lt;strong&gt;we get to know&lt;/strong&gt; that the &lt;strong&gt;person is impulsive&lt;/strong&gt; and he &lt;strong&gt;does things .... (in a negative manner)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;without rhyme or reason&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;means &lt;strong&gt;without any obvious reasonable explanation. (&lt;/strong&gt;बिना किसी स्पष्ट उचित स्पष्टीकरण के&lt;strong&gt;)&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He was sent behind the bars &lt;strong&gt;without rhyme or reason.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;rhyme or reason&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;means &lt;strong&gt;sense, logic, meaning, or planning.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;And when we &lt;strong&gt;add &amp;#39;without or with no&amp;#39; in the beginning&lt;/strong&gt;, it becomes&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;without any obvious reasonable explanation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;We will have to repent&amp;nbsp;if we do something &lt;strong&gt;without rhyme or reason.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Honest.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Fair and square:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;It is an idiomatic phrase that means&amp;nbsp;honestly and straightforwardly.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;We won the match fair and square.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrigible&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see the meanings of the given words-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Infallible-&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;Incapable of failure or error&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Incurable-&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;(of a sick person or a disease) is not able to be cured.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Inscrutable-&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;impossible to understand or interpret.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Incorrigible-&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;(of a person or their behaviour) very bad; too bad to be corrected or improved​.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, according to the meanings of the given words, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 4&amp;nbsp;i.e.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Incorrigible&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accentuate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;Fade&amp;#39;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;is a verb and it means&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;gradually grow faint and disappear&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. It might also mean &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;to become less prominent&lt;/strong&gt;.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;question&quot;&gt;For example, &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The colors had &lt;strong&gt;faded&lt;/strong&gt; and the paint was cracked, but those eyes were the same in the painting.&lt;/em&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The marked option &amp;#39;Accentuate&amp;#39; means &lt;span class=&quot;ng-binding&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;to &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;make (something) more noticeable or prominent; highlight&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For example, &amp;#39;&lt;em&gt;The thick moustache with twisted ends &lt;strong&gt;accentuated &lt;/strong&gt;the sharp angles of his cheekbones&lt;/em&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For example, &amp;#39;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;eg deg&quot;&gt;The new &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;policy&quot;&gt;policy&lt;/span&gt; only &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;serves&quot;&gt;serves&lt;/span&gt; to &lt;strong&gt;accentuate &lt;/strong&gt;the &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;inadequacy&quot;&gt;inadequacy&lt;/span&gt; of &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;help&quot;&gt;help&lt;/span&gt; for the &lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; title=&quot;homeless&quot;&gt;homeless&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;eg deg&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;eg deg&quot;&gt;So, we can see that &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Accentuate&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; can function as the opposite word of&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Fade&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;eg deg&quot;&gt;&amp;#39; in meaning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

