&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Discovery&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Breakthrough&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;an important discovery or development&lt;/strong&gt;. (कोई महत्वपूर्ण खोज या विकास)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Scientists are on the brink of a &lt;strong&gt;breakthrough&lt;/strong&gt; in the treatment of cancer&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​Let&amp;#39;s see the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;meaning&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of other given options:-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Disaster&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;any event that causes a lot of harm or damage&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;(महाविनाश, तबाही)
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;An Earthquake is a natural &lt;strong&gt;disaster&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Discovery&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;the action or process of discovering or being discovered&lt;/strong&gt;. (खोज)
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;After the scientist&amp;rsquo;s &lt;strong&gt;discovery&lt;/strong&gt;, people were cured of the deadly disease&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Coincidence&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;two or more similar things happening at the same time by chance, in a surprising way&lt;/strong&gt;. (दो या अधिक समान घटनाओं का संयोगवश और आश्&amp;zwj;चर्यजनक रूप से एक साथ घटित होना; सपांत, संयोग)
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;By &lt;strong&gt;coincidence&lt;/strong&gt;, we both went to the same school&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Accident&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;an unpleasant event that happens unexpectedly and causes damage, injury, or death&lt;/strong&gt;. (दुर्घटना; घटना)
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Investigators are still trying to determine the cause of the &lt;strong&gt;accident&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;synonyms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Breakthrough&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Discovery, Find, Innovation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antonyms&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Breakthrough&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Breakdown, Collapse, Crash&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option (2).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrase&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;on the ball&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is an idiomatic expression in English.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It means &lt;strong&gt;to be alert, attentive, knowledgeable; and quick to understand and react to a situation. (&lt;/strong&gt;किसी भी परिवर्तन या विकास से अवगत रहें और उन पर त्वरित प्रतिक्रिया दें&lt;strong&gt;)&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For example:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;if a person solves a problem at work very quickly, a colleague may say - &amp;quot;You&amp;#39;re really &lt;strong&gt;on the ball&lt;/strong&gt; today!&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;on the ball&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;means to be aware of any changes or developments and quick to react to them.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Only option (2) suggests the exact meaning of the given idiom.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Aware of any changes or developments and quick to react to them&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;We can remember this idiom in this way. A batsman&amp;nbsp;always keeps his eye on the ball.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;To bear the negative consequences of wrongful actions.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;To face the music&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is an idiom that means to accept the consequences of one&amp;#39;s actions, especially when they are negative. (किसी के कार्यों के परिणामों को स्वीकार करना, खासकर जब वे नकारात्मक हों)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;If she lied to me, then she&amp;#39;ll just have &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;to face the music&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;So, the most appropriate meaning of the given idiom is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;To bear the negative consequences of wrongful actions.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is Option 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;leisurely&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;&quot; /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot; display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;lsquo;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;hectic&lt;/span&gt;&amp;rsquo;(adjective) means-&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;very busy with a lot of things that you have to do quickly&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;. (&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;अत्&amp;zwj;यधिक व्&amp;zwj;यस्&amp;zwj;त, प्रायः बहुत से कार्य शीघ्र करते हुए&lt;/span&gt;)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;E.g:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;The area has become a haven for people tired of the &lt;strong&gt;hectic &lt;/strong&gt;pace of city life.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s have a look at the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;meaning&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the words that are given in the options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;leisurely&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(adjective)- &amp;ldquo;without hurry&amp;rdquo;. (&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;फु़रसत वाला, विश्रामपूर्ण, चैनभरा&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;chaotic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(adjective)- &amp;ldquo;in a state of chaos&amp;rdquo;. (&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;अव्&amp;zwj;यवस्थित, अस्&amp;zwj;त व्&amp;zwj;यस्&amp;zwj;त&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;forthright&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(adjective)- &amp;ldquo;saying exactly what you think in a clear and direct way&amp;rdquo;. (&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;अपनी सोच की सही अभिव्&amp;zwj;यक्ति में समर्थ; खरा-खरा कहने वाला, स्&amp;zwj;पष्&amp;zwj;टवादी&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;explicit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(adjective)- &amp;ldquo;clear, making something easy to understand&amp;rdquo;.&amp;nbsp;(&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;सुव्&amp;zwj;यक्त, समझने में सरल&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lsquo;leisurely&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;correct antonym&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the given bold word.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antonyms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the given word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;hectic&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;are-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;leisurely&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;calm&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;peace&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;easeful&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;unhurried&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;,&amp;nbsp;etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;synonyms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the given word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;hectic&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;are- &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;chaotic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;boisterous&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;animated&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;hassle&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;,&amp;nbsp;etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;hectic&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; in a sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Things are getting a bit &lt;strong&gt;hectic &lt;/strong&gt;for me at the moment.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;Respect&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word from the provided list that means &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;esteem&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;Respect.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In this context, esteem refers to&lt;strong&gt; respect and admiration for someone or something.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Respect suggests a deep admiration for someone or something elicited by their abilities, qualities, or achievements, which mirrors the definition of esteem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;Option 1&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Enmity&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;refers to a state or feeling of active opposition or hostility.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Elegance&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; pertains to the quality of being graceful and stylish in appearance or manner.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Famous&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;refers to the state of being known or recognized by many people.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 2&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&quot;abolish&quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to formally put an end to a system, practice, or institution. (समाप्त करना)
    &lt;ul&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The government decided to abolish the outdated law.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&quot;Cancel&quot; &lt;/strong&gt;refers to deciding or announcing that a planned event will not take place or that an agreement is no longer valid. (रद्द करना)
    &lt;ul&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The meeting was cancelled due to unforeseen circumstances.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Hence, we can infer that the synonym of &lt;strong&gt;&#039;abolish&#039; &lt;/strong&gt;is &lt;strong&gt;&#039;cancel&#039;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assist &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;मदद करना&lt;/span&gt;): To help or aid someone.
    &lt;ul&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; She assisted her friend in completing the project.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Subside &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;शांत होना&lt;/span&gt;): To become less intense, violent, or severe.
    &lt;ul&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The storm began to subside after a few hours.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Worship&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;पूजा करना&lt;/span&gt;): The feeling or expression of reverence and adoration for a deity.
    &lt;ul&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The community gathered to worship at the temple.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;option 2), i.e., &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;To be in the same difficult situation as someone else.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​The phrase&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;in the same boat&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;means to be in a troublesome situation like other people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For example:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;The teacher scolded the students for not doing their homework, and they were all &lt;strong&gt;in the same boat.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;During the pandemic, many people lost their job as they were&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;in the same boat.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;no longer useful.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Out of date&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;: No longer valid&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;u&gt;E.g.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;I must renew my passport. It&amp;rsquo;s &lt;strong&gt;out of date.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&amp;#39;no longer useful.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Miserly&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;generous&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means showing a readiness to give more of something, especially money, than is strictly necessary or expected. (उदार)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;She was very &lt;strong&gt;generous &lt;/strong&gt;with her time and helped everyone in need.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Miserly&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;refers to a person who is reluctant to spend money, typically because of greed. (कंजूस)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;miserly &lt;/strong&gt;old man refused to donate even a penny to charity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, we can infer that the opposite of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;generous&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;miserly&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Affluent &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;धनी&lt;/span&gt;): Having a great deal of money; wealthy.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The &lt;strong&gt;affluent &lt;/strong&gt;family donated a large sum to the charity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rich &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;समृद्ध &lt;/span&gt;): Possessing a large amount of money or valuable possessions.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;She became &lt;strong&gt;rich &lt;/strong&gt;after inheriting her grandfather&amp;#39;s estate.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wealthy&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;समृद्ध&lt;/span&gt;): Having a lot of money, possessions, or resources.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The &lt;strong&gt;wealthy &lt;/strong&gt;businessman owns several properties around the world.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
